@startuml
!theme plain
autonumber

title LLM Chatbot Protection Framework - Conceptual Run Flow

actor User
participant "CLI" as CLI
participant "Test Run\n(DefaultTest / Test)" as TestRun
participant "Test Cases" as TestCases
participant "Attack Generation\n+ Enhancement" as AttackFlow
participant "Chatbots" as Chatbots
participant "Evaluation + Guardrails" as Evaluation
participant "Storage / Summary" as Storage

== Baseline Run ==

User -> CLI: run-baseline
CLI -> TestRun: create suite and start run()
activate TestRun

TestRun -> TestCases: iterate configured test cases

loop for each test case
    TestCases -> AttackFlow: load or generate attacks
    AttackFlow --> TestCases: attacks + enhanced variants

    TestCases -> Chatbots: execute attacks
    note right of Chatbots
      Chatbots may use:
      - plain prompting
      - RAG context
      - attack documents
      - optional tools
    end note
    Chatbots --> TestCases: chatbot responses

    TestCases -> Evaluation: score responses and run guardrails
    Evaluation --> TestCases: baseline result + protection result

    TestCases -> Storage: write testcase JSON
end

TestRun -> Storage: write run result.json
Storage --> CLI: persisted run
deactivate TestRun

== Summary ==

User -> CLI: summarize-run
CLI -> Storage: load stored testcase JSON files
Storage -> Storage: aggregate per chatbot,\nper guardrail, per category,\nper technique
Storage --> CLI: summary JSON + CSV

@enduml
